.TH New-HomebridgeLocation 1 "October 2025" "docker-homebridge" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
New-HomebridgeLocation \- Generate certificate request and Homebridge YAML for a location
.SH SYNOPSIS
New-HomebridgeLocation [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generates a certificate request (certificate-request.conf) and a Homebridge YAML file (homebridge-LOCATION.yaml) for the specified LOCATION. Places the certificate request in secrets/certificates/LOCATION/ and the YAML file in the workspace root.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B --location
Set the location name (e.g., us-wa)
.TP
.B --country-code
Country code (default: US)
.TP
.B --state-or-province
State or province (default: Washington)
.TP
.B --city
City (default: Redmond)
.TP
.B --organization-name
Organization name (default: The Noble Family)
.TP
.B --organizational-unit
Organizational unit (default: 5028 243rd Ave NE)
.TP
.B --domain-name
Domain name (default: home.thenoble.family)
.TP
.B --email-address
Email address (default: network-admin@thenoble.family)
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information and exit
.SH USAGE
LOCATION=us-wa ./build/New-HomebridgeLocation
.SH AUTHOR
NobleFactor